<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-347-526  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 347 526.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 9 1990 n362 p113(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software-user survey: familiar names, faces to dominate. (BearStearns' corporate software user survey) (Corporate Closeup)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Doyle, T.C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A corporate software user survey conducted by Bear Stearns findsthat WordPerfect, Microsoft, Ashton-Tate, Novell and LotusDevelopment Corp will continue to dominate the microcomputersoftware market.andP;  The survey polled 1,550 corporate customers inbanking, insurance, finance and other key fields.andP;  Lotus continuesto depend on sales of its 1-2-3 spreadsheet program despiteexpansion of its product lines.andP;  Novell is expected to continue todominate the local area network operating software market,particularly as more users migrate to NetWare 386.andP;  Growth in theLAN server market and the introduction of more powerful machineshas not affected the average number of users per machine, whichcontinues to hover between eight and 30, according to the survey.andO;Banyan Systems topped the customer-satisfaction category, while3Com came out on the bottom in terms of satisfied customers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bear Stearns Companies Inc. (surveys).andO;Ticker:    BSC.andO;Topic:     User SurveySoftware PackagesMicrocomputersCompaniesOutlookSoftware Selection.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>